    "sourceFigure": "Fig. 1E",
    "note": "Re-digitized from Fig. 1E (the per-dye ΔF/F–V curves) on 2025: the figure steps the command voltage from −110 to +50 mV in 20-mV increments, so the data points are at [−110,−90,−70,−50,−30,−10,10,30,50] mV with −70 mV as the 0% baseline. Each curve was traced by HSV color separation of the source image (dye→hue mapping verified from the in-plot legend dots: JF503≈114° green, JF525≈70° lime, JF549≈59° yellow, JF585≈41° amber/orange, JF635≈10° red), cross-checked by eye. Voltron525 (main curve) is the most voltage-sensitive (−22% for the −70→+30 mV step, matching the paper's −23± 1% in the main text); Voltron635 the least (−7% at +30). Voltron549 and Voltron585 nearly coincide (within ~1–2% of each other across the range) and both sit between Voltron503 and Voltron525. The Voltron503 curve was added in this pass (previously omitted). Replaces an earlier digitization whose voltage grid (−100,−80,−70,−60,−40,−20,0,30,50) did not match the figure's 20-mV step points and whose JF585 curve was read too shallow (−16% vs ≈22% at +50 mV).",
    "proofread": false
  },
